1 unit(s) Avocado
1 pot(s) Ballymaloe Tomato Relish
2 unit(s) Brioche Buns
200 grams Grilling Cheese
1 unit(s) Lime
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper
unit(s) Egg (Optional)
to taste Oil

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.
Halve the avocado and remove the pit. Use a tablespoon to scoop out the flesh into a bowl. Mash with a fork. Season with salt and pepper.
Halve the lime.
Season the smashed avocado to taste with salt, pepper and a squeeze of lime juice.
Mix well and set aside.
TIP: To avoid turning on the oven, toast the bread in the toaster instead.

Place a pan (preferably non-stick) over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.
Chop the cheese into thin slices.
Once hot, fry until golden, 2-3 mins each side.
Pop the buns into the oven to warm through, 2-3 mins.
TIP: For an optional egg, place a pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil. Crack in your egg (1 per person) and fry until the white is cooked and the yolk is your desired firmness, 4-5 mins. Adjust heat as needed.

Spread the Ballymaloe relish evenly over the bun base.
Top with the avocado and cheese slices.
If you've made one, add your optional egg.
Sandwich closed with the bun lid.